claim.claim-text:
1. A method of forming a semiconductor device, the method comprising:
forming an electrostatic discharge (ESD) device region within a semiconductor body;
forming a first ESD device in a first region of the ESD device region; and
forming a second ESD device in a second region of the ESD device region;
forming a first trench in the semiconductor body, the second region being separated from the first region by the first trench;
lining sidewalls of the first trench with an insulator liner; and
filling the first trench at least partially with a conductive material.
